Task 4: Create a Form and Validate It
Explanation:
Design a form for job application or contact purposes. It should:
• Include fields: Name, Email, Phone, Message
• Perform basic validation using JavaScript (e.g., email format, empty fields)
Bonus: Use CSS to make it visually appealing.


###Index.html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Job Application Form</title>

<link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>

<body>

<div class="container">

<h1>Job Application Form</h1>

<form id="applicationForm">

<div class="input-group">
<label>Full Name</label>
<input type="text" id="name">
</div>

<div class="input-group">
<label>Email</label>
<input type="email" id="email">
</div>

<div class="input-group">
<label>Phone Number</label>
<input type="text" id="phone">
</div>

<div class="input-group">
<label>Message</label>
<textarea id="message" rows="5"></textarea>
</div>

<button type="submit">
Submit Application
</button>

</form>

<p id="result"></p>

</div>

<script src="script.js"></script>

</body>
</html>

